Values of constants remain unchanges during the program.

* You must initialize a constant at the time of it's declaration.

Syntax:- const_name CONSTANT Datatype := value;

Example:-
DECLARE

v_num CONSTANT NUMBER(7,6):= 3.141452;
BEGIN

    -- v_num := 3.141452; do not do this
    dbms_output.put_line(v_num);
END;


/


-- NOT NULL and DEFAULT
DECLARE

v_num CONSTANT NUMBER(7,6) DEFAULT 3.141452;
BEGIN

    -- v_num := 3.141452; do not do this
    dbms_output.put_line(v_num);
END;
